input.value:
fetch logs
| filter k8s.namespace.name == "karpenter"
| parse log, "JSON:log_karpenter"
| fieldsAdd message= log_karpenter[message], controller= log_karpenter[controller],karpentertime= log_karpenter[time], logger= log_karpenter[logger], karpenter_level= log_karpenter[level], karpenter_time= log_karpenter[time], source= log_karpenter[source], controllerGroup= log_karpenter[controllerGroup], error=log_karpenter[error], duration= log_karpenter[duration]
| fieldsRemove log_karpenter
| parse log, "BOS LD 'worker count' LD  INT:workercount LD   EOS"
| fields message, controller, time=toTimestamp(karpentertime), logger, karpenter_level, source,controllerGroup, error, duration, workercount
| sort time  desc

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{nodepool}, filter:matchesValue(resource_type, "cpu"), avg(karpenter_nodepools_usage)
| fieldsAdd value.A = arrayAvg(`avg(karpenter_nodepools_usage)`)
| limit 20

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{provider, controller, method}, avg(karpenter_cloudprovider_duration_seconds)
| fieldsAdd value.A = arrayAvg(`avg(karpenter_cloudprovider_duration_seconds)`)
| limit 20

timeseries by:{reason, nodepool}, avg(karpenter_nodepools_allowed_disruptions)
| fieldsAdd value.A = arrayAvg(`avg(karpenter_nodepools_allowed_disruptions)`)
| limit 20

metrics.description: The number of nodes for a given NodePool that can be concurrently disrupting at a point in time. Labeled by NodePool. Note that allowed disruptions can change very rapidly, as new nodes may be created and others may be deleted at any point.

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{nodepool, namespace, name}, sum(karpenter_pods_state)
| fieldsAdd value.A = arrayAvg(`sum(karpenter_pods_state)`)
| limit 20

metrics.description: Pod state is the current state of pods. This metric can be used several ways as it is labeled by the pod name, namespace, owner, node, nodepool name, zone, architecture, capacity type, instance type and pod phase.

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{nodepool, instance_size}, filter:matchesValue(resource_type, "cpu"), sum(karpenter_nodes_total_daemon_requests)
| fieldsAdd value.A = arrayAvg(`sum(karpenter_nodes_total_daemon_requests)`)
| limit 20

metrics.description: Node total daemon requests are the resource requested by DaemonSet pods bound to nodes.

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{nodepool, instance_size}, filter:matchesValue(resource_type, "memory"), sum(karpenter_nodes_total_daemon_requests)
| fieldsAdd value.A = arrayAvg(`sum(karpenter_nodes_total_daemon_requests)`)
| limit 20

metrics.description: Node total daemon requests are the resource requested by DaemonSet pods bound to nodes.

input.value: timeseries values = sum(dt.kubernetes.container.cpu_throttled), by:

metrics.description: This metric measures the total CPU throttling by container. The most detailed level of aggregation is container.

input.value: timeseries values = sum(dt.kubernetes.container.cpu_throttled), by: { k8s.pod.name}

timeseries usage = sum(dt.kubernetes.container.cpu_usage, default:0, rollup:avg), nonempty:true, by:{ k8s.deployment.name}, filter:  k8s.deployment.name == "recommendationservice", from: -1h 
| append[timeseries thrott = sum(dt.kubernetes.container.cpu_throttled, default:0, rollup:avg), nonempty:true, by:{k8s.deployment.name}, filter: k8s.deployment.name == "recommendationservice", from: -1h ]
| summarize avgusage=avg(usage[]), avgthottl=avg(thrott[])
| fields ratio= avgthottl[]/avgusage[]

leftYAxisSettings.label: Kubernetes: Container - CPU usage  Kubernetes: Container - CPU throttled  Kubernetes: Container - CPU requests  Kubernetes: Container - CPU limits

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{k8s.deployment.name}, filter:k8s.deployment.name == "recommendationservice", from:-1h, nonempty:TRUE, usage = sum(dt.kubernetes.container.cpu_usage, rollup:avg, default:0)
| append [timeseries by:{k8s.deployment.name}, filter:k8s.deployment.name == "recommendationservice", from:-1h, nonempty:TRUE, thrott = sum(dt.kubernetes.container.cpu_throttled, rollup:avg, default:0)]
| summarize avgusage = avg(usage[]), avgthottl = avg(thrott[])
| fields ratio = avgthottl[] / avgusage[]
grail.query:

| append[timeseries thrott = sum(dt.kubernetes.container.cpu_throttled, default:0, rollup:avg), nonempty:true, by:{k8s.deployment.name}, filter: k8s.deployment.name == "recommendationservice", from: -1h ]
